column1: Good evening.  Hope you are well.  I am interested in an apartment.  I saw the listing, and am wondering if this is a 1, 2 or 3 bedroom apartment? We have all thee options available right now, although at this time we only have a couple of 3 bedroom apartments. How many bedrooms are you looking for? I would most likely be interested in a two bedroom apartment.  If we could get a unit with a walk-in pantry, I would be willing to offer $2,000 for it. Our two bedroom units are priced at $2,300. It includes the heat, water and garbage. These apartments have great floor plans with walk-in pantry and all new appliances. Would you like to come take a tour? I would love to come take a tour.  I am just concerned that $2,300 might be a little too steep for me to afford right now.  I am a landscaper by trade.  Is there anyway I would be able to provide my landscaping services for Garden Village Apartments in return for getting the apartment at $2,000?  I do really nice work! We have a contract with our own landscaping company. We can offer you $100 discount per month if you sign a 12 months lease, providing that your application is approved. I think you will be impressed with our property and all the amenities that we offer. That sounds reasonable.  I will be willing to go for the $2,200 per month, with a 12 month lease. Great! Please let me know when you would like to come take a tour. Also please bring your picture ID and your income verification (2 latest pay stubs or bank statement). Looking forward to seeing you.

column1: Hey, I'm interested in this item but I'm on a budget. Is your list price your final offer? This bike is a great deal as you can see from the description.  I feel as though $800 is a reasonable asking price considering the high end components. The frame looks great, but I'm concerned about maintenance costs and more fragile components. Would you be interested if I delivered it to you for free and dropped the price to $775? Free delivery is a perk to me, but I think the parts you've listed are only worth about $500. That is a very big discount.  I will add free delivery, maintenance for three months and a final price of $750. That's not a very big price drop. What about $600? The lowest I will go is $700 and no other perks. That's just too high for me. Are you sure? $700 is more than fair. Can you tell me anything more about the bike that will convince me of that? All I see is a 2009 aluminum frame, the crankset, and the handlebars and stem. It has Shimano Devore XT crankset, Ritchie's Comp handlebars and stem, Avid Juicy 7 Hydrolic Disc Brakes.  These are all high end components. Ah, I didn't know about the brakes! That makes a big difference for me. I'm willing to pay $650, in cash if you'd prefer, and pick it up myself. $690 and it is yours. Are you willing to go just a bit lower, perhaps $675? Ok, it's a deal at $675! I agree! But for some reason, I can't submit the offer from my end. Are you able to do so?
